  <h2>It creates better, more sustainable websites</h2>
  <p>Websites grow and evolve over time. By structuring your content and representing that structure to users in the navigation, you will:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>help more users find good information</li>
    <li>increase the number of people who successfully self-serve</li>
    <li>make it easier and less time-consuming for editors to manage, maintain and reference content</li>
    <li>create a more sustainable publishing platform, better prepared for future innovations</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="it-gives-users-context">It gives users context</h2>

  <p>It underpins user experience by helping users with:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>placemaking</li>
    <li>orientation</li>
    <li>navigation</li>
    <li>search</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Placemaking</h3>
  <p>Placemaking is about users understanding what the website is for and what it offers. The way you group, name and display content helps people understand the scope of the website and how useful it will be to them.</p>

